  "prompt": "Why do IIT's and NIT's in India get so much domestic admiration when most of them do not feature anywhere in top 100 globally?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why IITs (Indian Institutes of Technology) and NITs (National Institutes of Technology) are highly regarded in India:\n\n1. Historical Significance\n- Established during nation-building era\n- Played crucial role in developing India's technical workforce\n- Symbols of India's post-independence technological aspirations\n\n2. Extremely Competitive Entrance\n- Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) is one of world's toughest exams\n- Less than 1-2% candidates qualify\n- Reflects high academic standards and student caliber\n\n3. Alumni Success\n- Large number of alumni in top global tech companies\n- Many successful entrepreneurs and business leaders\n- Significant representation in Silicon Valley\n\n4. Government Recognition\n- Declared \"Institutes of National Importance\"\n- Receive substantial government funding and support\n- Perceived as premier national institutions\n\n5. Affordability\n- Significantly lower fees compared to international universities\n- High-quality education at relatively low cost\n\n6. Social Prestige\n- Getting admission considered a major achievement\n- High social status for students and families\n- Seen as pathway to upward social mobility\n\n7. Strong Industry Connections\n- Good placement records\n- Strong industry-institute collaboration\n- High starting salaries for graduates\n\nWhile global rankings might not reflect their true potential, domestic reputation remains very strong.",
